g.title: FIND_WALL_BACK_INDEX
g.text: FIND_WALL_BACK_INDEX

g.title: cluster_FIND_BACK_WALL_CELL
g.text: FIND_BACK_WALL_CELL

g.title: COMMENT_8d77600+1
g.text: !> brief Find the back wall cell for a given wall cell.
!> param NM Mesh number
!> param IW Wall cell index
!> details If the exposed back wall cell is in another mesh, store the cell info into arrays that are to be MPI exchanged.

g.title: COMMENT_8daaa40+1
g.text: Do not apply HT3D to VARIABLE_THICKNESS exterior boundary

g.title: COMMENT_8d9f6e0+1
g.text: For VARIABLE_THICKNESS and HT3D cases, get material information from obstruction

g.title: COMMENT_8daa8a0+1
g.text: Determine the index of the obstruction (OBST_INDEX) that occupies the cell with index IC.
If the obstruction is thin, search all obstructions in the mesh for one that corresponds to the upwind cell face.

g.title: COMMENT_8dbc120+1
g.text: If this is a thin obstruction, use its actual user-specified coordinates to determine THICKNESS

g.title: COMMENT_8dd2760+1
g.text: Determine if the back face is found

g.title: COMMENT_8f07f40+1
g.text: If 1-D solid and the user-specified thickness is less than the current thickness, abandon the search for back-wall cell

g.title: COMMENT_8f0e360+1
g.text: If the user has specified LINING materials (HT3D or VARIABLE_THICKNESS with SURF MATLs and THICKNESS), add this information to
existing lists of layers and materials.

g.title: COMMENT_8f0e760+1
g.text: Offset the coordinates of the wall face to account for linings

g.title: COMMENT_8f21760+1
g.text: Copy the front face SURF layer information into the holding arrays

g.title: COMMENT_8f2c000+1
g.text: Add layers that are associated with the underlying OBSTructions

g.title: COMMENT_8f41960+1
g.text: Add layers from the back surface lining

g.title: COMMENT_8f4e000+1
g.text: Reallocate ONE_D arrays holding layer and material info for HT3D and VARIABLE_THICKNESS objects
